name: BiomeSize
description: BiomeSize is fired when vanilla Minecraft attempts to generate biomes. This event is fired during biome generation in GenLayer#initializeAllBiomeGenerators(long, WorldType). originalSize the original size of the Biome. newSize the new size of the biome. Initially set to the originalSize . If newSize is set to a new value, that value will be used for the Biome size. This event is not Cancelable . This event does not have a result. HasResult This event is fired on the MinecraftForge#TERRAIN_GEN_BUS .
